What is Cloud Security?
ans: Cloud security is a set of polices, technologies, control and design procedure to protect cloud-based system, data and infrastructure from external and internal threat.

Cloud security Threats:
i. data breches
ii. data loss
iii. account hijacking
iv. denial of service
v. insecure APIs
vi. malicious Insider
vii. abuse of cloud services
viii. shared technology issue

What is Security as Service?
ans: Security as Service is a cloud delivery model where third party provider integrate their security services into your infrastructure on a subscription basis. It allows organiation to outsource the management of security tools rather than maintaining the  m on- premises.
Example
Identity and Access management (IAM)
Data Loss and prevention (DLP)
Web security
email security

Benefit:
cost effective
constant update
experties

